The last `sorry` is inside the proof of `LocallyIntegrable (RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ f) μ`.
The goal at this point is `LocallyIntegrable (RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ f) μ`.
The relevant hypothesis is `hf : @MeasureTheory.MemLorentz α NNReal m0 instENormedSpaceNNReal.toENorm NNReal.instTopologicalSpace f p 1 μ`.
`hf` states that `f` is in the Lorentz space `L^{p,1}(μ)`.
A function `f` in `L^{p,1}(μ)` is, by definition, locally integrable with respect to `μ`.
The standard way to prove this is to use the fact that `f ∈ L^{p,1}(μ)` implies `f` is locally `L^1` (because `p ≥ 1` is implicitly used in the definition of `L^{p,1}`), and `L^1` local integrability implies `L^p` local integrability.
