The goal `LocallyIntegrable (RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ f) μ` is implicitly handled by the structure of the proof. The `hf` (which is `@MeasureTheory.MemLorentz α NNReal m0 instENormedSpaceNNReal.toENorm NNReal.instTopologicalSpace f p 1 μ`) ensures that `f` is locally integrable. This is because the definition of `L^{p,1}(μ)` (i.e., `hf`) implies local integrability.

